    {
        "control_id": "BCM_002",
        "control_name": "Ransomware protection - backups",
        "vodafone_standard": "Tier 2 SSMP (CYBER_038) Section 5.7: Ransomware protection - backups",
        "domain": "BCM",
        "d_statements": [
            {"id": "D1", "text": "The scope of mission critical data to be covered by this control has been clearly defined and documented based on a formal impact assessment with a focus on availability. This includes but is not limited to  - data needed to keep Mission Critical Activities alive (as defined in the Business Continuity Management Policy v2.2 or later); and  - data needed to recover systems in line with SLA targets after a major disaster (as defined in the Technology Resilience Policy v3.3.1 or later)."},
            {"id": "D2", "text": "Backup storage, backup systems and backup administration systems have been hardened and patched in line with requirements for controls Compliance of systems with hardening standards and Patching."},
            {"id": "D3", "text": "Multi factor authentication must be implemented for administrators accessing backup storage, backup administration systems and the backup systems as applicable in line with requirements for controls Multi-factor authentication. Privileged credentials which provide the capability to bypass / overwrite immutability must be covered by a PAM solution which provides at least vaulting capabilities (see controls Privileged access management + for further details)."},
            {"id": "D4", "text": "Communication between the backup storage and the production environment is restricted through network segregation.  Where technically feasible, the initiation of connections from the backup storage to productions systems should be blocked."},
            {"id": "D5", "text": "The backup storage file system is “immutable” to protect the integrity of the backup data, e.g. through mechanisms like  - restrictions for execution of destructible commands by using non standard or “invisible” file systems which can only be accessed via an API or non standard protocols; and / or  - successful execution of deletion commands requiring knowledge of backup record IDs; and / or  - use of Write Once Read Many (WORM) storage solutions or Cloud Cold Backups."},
            {"id": "D6", "text": "A cyber incident response plan has been established for ransomware attacks and linked with the backup process, e.g. to check if backup systems are affected as well with a response time of few hours."},
            {"id": "D7", "text": "For cloud environments, mission critical data must be backed up in line with requirements D1 - D6 as applicable. Versioning can be used as alternative mechanism to protect backups. Administrative functions (e.g. activation / deactivation of backups, configuration of retention periods) must be protected by multi factor authentication. Deletion protection must be in place for backups / versions. Credentials which provide the capability to bypass / overwrite immutability must be covered by a PAM solution which provides at least vaulting capabilities."},
        ],
        "e_statements": [
            {"id": "E1", "text": "- Extract of asset register (or equivalent) with sampled data source tagged as mission critical.   - Business impact assessment \"BIA\" for sampled data source supporting the above classification."},
            {"id": "E2", "text": "- Report from hardening / compliance management tool (e.g. CCS) demonstrating that backup systems comply with the hardening policy and approved exception documents for deviations found.  - Patching status report for backup systems demonstrating that critical/high security patches have been installed in line with the Patching policy (e.g. Microsoft MCS report)."},
            {"id": "E3", "text": "Evidence that access to backup systems require MFA and that privileged credentials which provide the capability to bypass / overwrite immutability have been onboarded to PAM for vaulting."},
            {"id": "E4", "text": "- Network diagrams showing that backup storage are separated from the production systems through network segregation.  - Optional: Screenshot demonstrating that a connection attempt from the backup storage to a production system is being rejected."},
            {"id": "E5", "text": "- Screenshot from backup solution showing combination of settings making backup data \"immutable\" (see D6 for examples)."},
            {"id": "E6", "text": "- Extract from cyber incident response plan, mandating a synchronisation with the backup teams as soon as ransomware attack is detected.  - Sample incident showing that the backup teams got involved within a few hours after the attack was detected."},
            {"id": "E7", "text": "Only applicable to sample for cloud-based data source:  - Provide evidence in line with E1 to E6.  Or  - Screenshots / reports demonstrating that deletion protection is in place for backups or versions, that access to administrative functions require MFA and that privileged credentials which provide the capability to bypass / overwrite immutability have been onboarded to PAM for vaulting."},
        ],
    },
