    {
        "control_id": "GENERAL_002",
        "control_name": "Management of technical vulnerabilities",
        "vodafone_standard": "Tier 2 Cyber Security Testing (CYBER_040)",
        "domain": "General",
        "d_statements": [
            {"id": "D1", "text": "Policies and standards are in place defining the frequency of vulnerability scans, the scoring model to prioritise findings and a remediation process with target timelines - depending on the criticality and location of affected systems / services and vulnerabilities found."},
            {"id": "D2", "text": "External and internal vulnerability scans are being performed on a regular basis according to the relevant policies and standards."},
            {"id": "D3", "text": "Vulnerability scans are being performed for new systems / services. Any critical / high vulnerabilities identified are remediated and re-tested before go live. This includes confirmed and potential vulnerabilities."},
            {"id": "D4", "text": "Vulnerabilities found are being analysed, prioritised and addressed by a remediation (e.g. through patching, system upgrades or configuration changes), implementation of compensating controls and / or (for vulnerabilities rated medium or low) risk acceptance process as required in a timely manner according to the relevant policies and standards. This includes confirmed and potential vulnerabilities."},
            {"id": "D5", "text": "Vulnerability scans are being re-performed to confirm if remediation activities have been successful and the corresponding vulnerabilities can be closed."},
            {"id": "D6", "text": "KPI reports are available to management to monitor on a regular basis vulnerabilities found and their status and to take corrective actions in a timely manner as required."},
        ],
        "e_statements": [
            {"id": "E1", "text": "- Central: Global Cyber Security Testing Policy.  - Local Market/Entity: Confirm vulnerability management policy in use. If different to Global policy, provide a copy of the documented vulnerability management policy, with excerpts or page references covering frequency of scans, scoring model to prioritise findings, and a remediation process with target timelines depending on the criticality of affected systems / services and severity of vulnerabilities found. If local policy is used, evidence that it is aligned with or has stricter requirements than global policy requirements."},
            {"id": "E2", "text": "- Central: Evidence of scanning schedule.  - Local Market/Entity: Copies of vulnerability scan reports for each system in the sample. Report confirming that scans are carried out in line with the relevant policies, standards and schedule."},
            {"id": "E3", "text": "- Local Market/Entity: Evidence of the number of new systems deployed in the last 3 months along with evidence of the number of systems that have been signed off and have had vulnerability scans prior to go live.   - Local Market/Entity: Vulnerability scan reports and sign-off to be provided for chosen samples.   - Local Market/Entity: Evidence that vulnerabilities found have been remediated and retested before go live."},
            {"id": "E4", "text": "- Local Markets/Entity: For the vulnerabilities found in the sampled systems, a copy of the remediation activities undertaken, showing the timeline in which they were carried out, based on the severity of the vulnerability.   - Local Markets/Entity: Evidence of any compensating controls or (for vulnerabilities rated as medium or low) risk acceptance confirming that vulnerability can't be fixed within policy timelines. Where risks have been accepted, evidence that this has been recorded and is tracked on a risk register."},
            {"id": "E5", "text": "Local Markets/Entity: Confirmation that the remediation actions identified for the sampled systems were successful in closing the vulnerability identified and did not introduce new vulnerabilities."},
            {"id": "E6", "text": "- Central: Evidence that KPI reporting from central tooling is circulated to Local Markets.  - Local Markets/Entity: Evidence that corrective actions for open vulnerabilities are tracked and communicated to management regularly."},
        ],
    },
